        "action": "Extend Government funding to Transport for London (TfL) beyond 4 February",
        "additional_details": "The reasons have been written by him:\r\n \r\n\u2022\tClimate change: Without public transport car use will go up and London will not be able to reduce its CO2 emissions.\r\n\u2022\tJobs: People who can\u2019t afford cars won\u2019t be able to get to jobs and there will be a crisis.\r\n\u2022\tWhen a train approaches a platform, I wonder how the flawless machinery works. As soon as I get on a train I feel serene. I always look out of the window while dreaming of being a train driver.\r\n\u2022\tLots of children will be sad if TFL shuts down. Every country wants its children to be happy.\r\n",
        "background": "On behalf of my 8 yr old who wants the Government to extend its extraordinary funding to TfL beyond 4 Feb 2022 to help combat climate change and protect jobs.",
